  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">NGO Support / Promoting Child Rights Through Educational Settings</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The school enrolment ratio of children in Nepal is almost 87 percent, but still the drop out rate is also very high, almost 100 children enrolled in grade one only 22 percent appear the school leaving examination. Children experienced discrimination, have suffered violence on the name of discipline, are victims of political conflict and have suffered sexual abuse. The school curriculum is not children&#xC2;&#xB4;s right responsive and friendly. The project aims to promote and protect child rights in and through educational settings and policies with the active involvement of parents, community and children themselves. The project promotes significantly schools and other educational sectors role on promoting children&#xC2;&#xB4;s rights at local and national level and to ensure child rights in schools benefits children directly.</narrative>
  </description>
